import React, {useState} from 'react'
import { Navbar, Nav, Container } from 'react-bootstrap'
import { FaBars } from 'react-icons/fa'
import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css'
import './App.css'


function App () {
const [showNav, setShowNav] = useState(false)
const toggleNav = () => setShowNav(!showNav)
  return (
    <Navbar
      bg='dark'
      variant='dark'
      expand='lg'
      className={`navbar`}
    >
      <Container>
        <Navbar.Brand href='#home'>Brand</Navbar.Brand>
        <Navbar.Toggle
          aria-controls='basic-navbar-nav'
       
          className='menu-icon'
        >
          <FaBars />
        </Navbar.Toggle>
        <Navbar.Collapse
          id='basic-navbar-nav'
          className={'navbar-collapse'}
        >
          <Nav className='mr-auto'>
            <Nav.Link href='#home'>
              Home
            </Nav.Link>
            <Nav.Link href='#about' >
              About
            </Nav.Link>
            <Nav.Link href='#services' >
              Services
            </Nav.Link>
            <Nav.Link href='#contact' >
              Contact
            </Nav.Link>
          </Nav>
        </Navbar.Collapse>

        <Navbar.Collapse
          id='basic-navbar-nav2'
          className={`navbar-collapse2 ${ showNav ? 'show' : ''} `}
        >
          <Nav className='mr-auto'>
            <Nav.Link href='#home' >
              Home
            </Nav.Link>
            <Nav.Link href='#about' >
              About
            </Nav.Link>
            <Nav.Link href='#services' >
              Services
            </Nav.Link>
            <Nav.Link href='#contact' >
              Contact
            </Nav.Link>
          </Nav>
        </Navbar.Collapse>
      </Container>
    </Navbar>
  )
}

export default App
